                    <figcaption class="text-muted mt-2">Churn rate by usage decline level, highlighting usage decline as a critical early warning sign of potential churn.</figcaption>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <!-- Survival Analysis -->
    <div class="card visualization-card mb-5">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h4 class="card-title">2. Survival Analysis</h4>
            <p class="card-text">Survival analysis provided insights into customer retention patterns over time.  This the probability of customers surviving (or remaining active) in their future days using a product.</p>
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-6">
                    <div class="text-center">
                        <img src="static/images/churn/overall_survival_curve.png" alt="Overall Survival Curve" class="img-fluid viz-img">
                        <figcaption class="text-muted mt-2">Kaplan-Meier survival curve showing retention over time, with a drop in the first 90 days.</figcaption>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-6">
                    <div class="text-center">
                        <img src="static/images/churn/survival_by_subscription.png" alt="Survival by Subscription Type" class="img-fluid viz-img">
                        <figcaption class="text-muted mt-2">Survival curves by subscription type - higher retention rates for premium customers over time.</figcaption>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="mt-4">
                <div class="text-center">
                    <img src="static/images/churn/cox_hazard_ratios.png" alt="Cox Proportional Hazards" class="img-fluid viz-img" style="max-width: 800px;">
                    <figcaption class="text-muted mt-2">Cox Proportional Hazards model results showing the relative impact of different factors on churn risk (hazard ratios above 1 indicate increased risk).</figcaption>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="row mt-4">
                <div class="col-md-6">
                    <h5>Key Survival Analysis Insights</h5>
                    <ul>
                        <li>The steepest drop in the survival curve occurs in the first 90 days, highlighting this as a critical period for retention efforts</li>
                        <li>Premium subscribers have a 68% higher retention rate at the 12-month mark compared to Basic subscribers</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <!-- Predictive modelling Results -->
    <div class="card visualization-card mb-5">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h4 class="card-title">3. Predictive modelling Results</h4>
            <p class="card-text">A Random Forest classifier was developed to predict customer churn with high accuracy. The model identifies at-risk customers before they churn, enabling proactive retention efforts and providing insights into the most important predictors of churn behavior.</p>
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-6">
                    <div class="text-center">
